==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fulling
<hw>Full"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The process of cleansing,
shrinking, and thickening cloth by moisture, heat, and
pressure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fulling mill</b></col>, <cd>a mill for fulling cloth as
by means of pesties or stampers, which alternately fall into and rise
from troughs where the cloth is placed with hot water and fuller's
earth, or other cleansing materials.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>full-length</ent>⟦br⟧
